Remarks . Although we did not examine specimens of
Par. daviei
from its type locality ( Irian Jaya , Papua , Indonesia ) or the adjacent area, the Taiwanese specimens agree well with the original description (
Sakai et al . 2006
), including carapace ( Fig. 2A ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: figs. 77, 78), male chelae ( Fig. 2B ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 77), male infraorbital ridges ( Fig. 2C ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 66), and G1 ( Fig. 2 E–H;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 68).
